steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"b8g56","text":"General Rota-rod test is performed as follows: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9mmbj","text":"The rotarod apparatus (Panlab LE8205, Harvard Apparatus) equipped with a mouse rod (3 cm diameter)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9ghpo","text":"Set the rotarod with a start speed of 4 rpm, and set to 4–40 rpm acceleration over 300s","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"31j1o","text":"Hold the mouse by tail. Place the mouse on the rod and face away from the direction of rotation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7cj7b","text":"Start acceleration and record the time for each mouse to fall.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cl4fa","text":"Perform five trials with intertrial-interval = 15 s, max trial duration = 300 s (one daily session)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ntnk","text":"Calculate the average time to fall over five trials.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Details of dopamine signaling manipulations for Rota-rod
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"3v6va","text":"The specific task consists of eighteen daily sessions divided into two phases (Figure 1). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Details of dopamine signaling manipulations for Rota-rod
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"dqo9o","text":"Administer intraperitoneally dopamine receptor antagonists for sessions 1-5 30 min prior to testing prepared in 0.9% saline): cocktail of 1 mg/kg SCH23390 + 1 mg/kg eticlopride, 1 mg/kg SCH23390, or 1 mg/kg eticlopride.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"90kln","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Details of dopamine signaling manipulations for Rota-rod
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2qae8","text":"Following a 72-hr break, test the mice for another thirteen sessions (drug-free recovery phase)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8k6sr","text":"The open field arena (56 x 56 cm) is used to assess locomotor activity.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8lu08","text":"Turn on the lights in the recordingg chamber. Clean the arena with 70% ethanol and adjust the camera border to match the arena edge. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cnsf3","text":"Wait for 5min to allow the ethanol to evaporate completely prior test.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"626rs","text":"A mouse is placed in the center of the arena and its ambulation activity is collected by the LimeLight software for 20 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"58omv","text":"Clean the arena with 70% ethanol between tests. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"89a0a","text":"The LimeLight software provides the total distance traveled and the percentage of time/distance within different parts of the arena.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
